Aside from performance, there are two aspects of the announcement I found v=
ery notable.

First, Gemini was both trained on and does inference on Google=E2=80=99s in=
-house TPUs. Again from the announcement post ( https://blog.google/technol=
ogy/ai/google-gemini-ai/#scalable-efficient ) :

We trained Gemini 1.0 at scale on our AI-optimized infrastructure using Goo=
gle=E2=80=99s in-house designed Tensor Processing Units (TPUs) v4 and v5e. =
And we designed it to be our most reliable and scalable model to train, and=
 our most efficient to serve. On TPUs, Gemini runs significantly faster tha=
n earlier, smaller and less-capable models. These custom-designed AI accele=
rators have been at the heart of Google=E2=80=99s AI-powered products that =
serve billions of users like Search, YouTube, Gmail, Google Maps, Google Pl=
ay and Android. They=E2=80=99ve also enabled companies around the world to =
train large-scale AI models cost-efficiently.

Today, we=E2=80=99re announcing the most powerful, efficient and scalable T=
PU system to date, Cloud TPU v5p, designed for training cutting-edge AI mod=
els. This next generation TPU will accelerate Gemini=E2=80=99s development =
and help developers and enterprise customers train large-scale generative A=
I models faster, allowing new products and capabilities to reach customers =
sooner.

The best way to be GPU-rich ( https://www.semianalysis.com/p/google-gemini-=
eats-the-world-gemini ) is to not need GPUs at all; that is exactly where G=
oogle is thanks to its nearly decade-long investment in building its own te=
nsor-processing unit chips (TPUs). These are even simpler than GPUs, which =
helps them scale even better; the reason it works is because they are desig=
ned in conjunction with the models that run on them. This is a potentially =
huge advantage in the long run, both in terms of cost and scalability.

It also fits with Google=E2=80=99s long-running AI strategy in the consumer=
-space: yes, chatbots are very much a thing, thanks to ChatGPT, but Google =
has long argued =E2=80=94 and fairly so =E2=80=94 that many of the most com=
pelling use cases for AI are within the apps that people already use; those=
 apps have been built with TPUs in mind for years now.

