w ) : Apple is definitely going to lean into open source, and it=E2=80=99s =
easy to imagine MLX being built into Apple=E2=80=99s operating systems goin=
g forward.

This approach does assume Apple=E2=80=99s dominance in terms of devices: ML=
X needs to be used from the get-go in terms of building out a model, which =
means developers will need to do work, surely motivated by reaching Apple c=
onsumers; perhaps Apple is counting on the community to add it to PyTorch p=
roper so that Apple Silicon is supported natively.

What is notable is that this is all about leveraging Apple Silicon=E2=80=99=
s CPU and GPU, but not its own neural processing units: those are for low-p=
ower inference, and require a lot of optimization to use effectively; Apple=
, though, doesn=E2=80=99t control the models it is seeking to leverage to t=
hat extent. Yes, the company may have the best chips, but without its own m=
odels that won=E2=80=99t be quite as big of an advantage as it used to be.

Note the contrast to Google; when its Tensor smartphone chip first shipped =
